459. Int J Biomed Comput. 1978 May;9(3):215-28. doi:
10.1016/0020-7101(78)90035-1.

Robustness of life table methods in large populations--a study by computer 
simulation.

Mode CJ, Littman GS.

The robustness of the product life table estimator of the survival function was 
studied for large populations under perturbations in the age distribution, 
changing levels of mortality and changing patterns of fertility. A 
macrosimulation system, based on a class of stochastic population models called 
generalised age-dependent branching processes, was used to carry out the 
numerical investigations. Aside from drastic perturbations in the age 
distribution and changes in levels of mortality, the product life table 
estimator of the survival function was found to be robust in large populations, 
under a variety of conditions.

