486. J Am Vet Med Assoc. 1978 Sep 1;173(5 Pt 1):478-80.

Age and milk production data of cattle culled from a dairy herd with 
paratuberculosis.

Buergelt CD, Duncan JR.

Statistical assessment of age and milk production data revealed a significantly 
shorter life expectancy and reduced milk production of Mycobacterium 
paratuberculosis-infected dairy cows, when compared with non-infected herdmates. 
High producing cows were frequently culled after their 1st or 2nd gestation, 
contributing to an undetermined economic loss with regard to their potential 
breeding value. Cows with subclinical infection frequently had problems of 
infertility and of mastitis.

